For the Wales international of the 1980s see Steve Jones (rugby player born 1951) Steve Jones (born 20 April 1977, Neath) is a Welsh international rugby union player. A hooker, he has attained 5 international caps for the Wales national rugby union team. Jones was first capped for Wales against Japan in 2001. He currently plays for Newport Gwent Dragons after his contract was extended for a further two years in March 2010.[1] 
